-- Microsoft Says U.S. Stores Sold 193,000 Xbox Players in August
-- B y   C l i f f   E d w a r d s
-- 2012-09-06T22:13:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-06/microsoft-says-u-s-stores-sold-193-000-xbox-players-in-august.html
Microsoft Corp. (MSFT)  said U.S. retailers
sold 193,000 Xbox video-game consoles last month, citing data
from market researcher NPD Group Inc.  The sales represented 48 percent market share for current
generation consoles, Redmond, Washington-based Microsoft said
today in an e-mailed statement. Stores sold 308,000 Xbox players
in the same month a year ago, according to NPD data at the time.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cliff Edwards in  San Francisco  at 
